00:05:43,679 --> 00:05:44,847
Tasty!

60
00:05:46,908 --> 00:05:47,709
Tasty.

61
00:05:49,412 --> 00:05:50,119
Tasty.

62
00:05:51,374 --> 00:05:52,100
Tasty.

63
00:05:54,569 --> 00:05:55,360
Tasty.

64
00:05:57,825 --> 00:05:58,625
Tasty.

65
00:05:59,625 --> 00:06:01,180
That's the Flame Hashira?

66
00:06:01,287 --> 00:06:01,740
Tasty.

67
00:06:01,793 --> 00:06:02,610
Uh-huh.

68
00:06:02,944 --> 00:06:04,892
Not just some random glutton?

69
00:06:04,917 --> 00:06:05,578
Uh-huh.

70
00:06:06,185 --> 00:06:06,945
Tasty!

71
00:06:07,337 --> 00:06:09,407
Uh, 'scuse me, sir.

72
00:06:10,482 --> 00:06:11,262
Tasty.

73
00:06:11,563 --> 00:06:13,198
R-Rengoku?

74
00:06:13,772 --> 00:06:14,558
Tasty!

75
00:06:15,513 --> 00:06:17,289
Yeah, we heard you...

76
00:06:17,407 --> 00:06:18,828
the first 50 times.

77
00:06:26,244 --> 00:06:27,017
It's you.

78
00:06:27,484 --> 00:06:28,540
You were at the mansion.

79
00:06:29,274 --> 00:06:31,669
Yes. I'm Tanjiro Kamado.

80
00:06:32,315 --> 00:06:33,890
This is Zenitsu Agatsuma,

81
00:06:34,170 --> 00:06:37,090
and this here is Inosuke Hashibira.

82
00:06:37,976 --> 00:06:39,730
I see. Also...

83
00:06:40,037 --> 00:06:41,797
isn't there one in that box?

84
00:06:42,150 --> 00:06:44,833
Right, my sister Nezuko.

85
00:06:45,813 --> 00:06:48,117
Yes! I remember that demon.

86
00:06:48,778 --> 00:06:52,636
Since the Master accepted her, I will keep my peace.

87
00:06:56,786 --> 00:06:57,975
Sit down, won't you?

88
00:07:05,030 --> 00:07:08,113
Incredible! I'm actually inside of this titan!

89
00:07:08,138 --> 00:07:09,848
Would you calm down?!

90
00:07:09,873 --> 00:07:11,661
You're gonna break the glass like that!

91
00:07:12,139 --> 00:07:14,003
And what brings the three of you here?

92
00:07:15,158 --> 00:07:15,791
A mission?

93
00:07:16,525 --> 00:07:18,612
Yes. We were ordered to join you.

94
00:07:19,212 --> 00:07:21,268
We received a message from a Crow

95
00:07:21,815 --> 00:07:25,340
which let us know that casualties
on this train were on the rise.

96
00:07:25,667 --> 00:07:28,779
Ah! That's why you're here. Understood.

97
00:07:28,892 --> 00:07:29,692
Sir...

98
00:07:30,953 --> 00:07:32,994
there was one more thing...

99
00:07:34,089 --> 00:07:35,840
something I wanted to ask you.

100
00:07:37,367 --> 00:07:38,977
Oh? What is it?

101
00:07:40,026 --> 00:07:41,676
It's about my father.

102
00:07:42,231 --> 00:07:43,423
What about your father?

103
00:07:44,884 --> 00:07:46,546
He was a frail man.

104
00:07:46,946 --> 00:07:47,806
Was he, now?!

105
00:07:48,431 --> 00:07:49,466
And yet...

106
00:07:49,576 --> 00:07:52,940
he could perform a kagura dance in freezing weather.

107
00:07:53,260 --> 00:07:54,335
Well, good for him!

108
00:07:57,101 --> 00:07:57,747
And then...

109
00:07:57,893 --> 00:07:58,673
And then?!

110
00:07:59,473 --> 00:08:02,588
Hinokami Kagura, the dance...

111
00:08:03,554 --> 00:08:07,354
I found myself doing it, just like my father used to.

112
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:11,354
I was hoping if you knew anything about that dance,

113
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,488
you'd be willing to tell me.

114
00:08:19,402 --> 00:08:20,242
Certainly!

115
00:08:21,370 --> 00:08:22,203
But I don't!

116
00:08:22,629 --> 00:08:23,216
Huh?

117
00:08:23,876 --> 00:08:26,653
I have never even heard of that dance, not once.

118
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:30,809
Your father taking this kagura and adapting it for battle

119
00:08:31,128 --> 00:08:32,276
is commendable.

120
00:08:32,836 --> 00:08:34,688
There's nothing more to say about it!

121
00:08:35,154 --> 00:08:37,301
H-Hang on! Are you sure you can't think of...

122
00:08:37,414 --> 00:08:39,115
You should become my Tsuguko!

123
00:08:39,509 --> 00:08:40,756
I'll look after you!

124
00:08:40,916 --> 00:08:42,095
Not so fast!

125
00:08:42,168 --> 00:08:44,381
And wait! When'd you get so gigantic?!

126
00:08:45,541 --> 00:08:47,157
<i>He's a strange one, huh?</i>

127
00:08:47,582 --> 00:08:49,823
Flame Breathing has a long history.

128
00:08:50,383 --> 00:08:55,100
A Hashira of flame and of water have always existed.

129
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,175
Flame...

130
00:08:57,834 --> 00:08:58,401
Water...

131
00:08:58,740 --> 00:08:59,477
Wind...

132
00:08:59,945 --> 00:09:00,712
Stone...

133
00:09:00,865 --> 00:09:01,805
and Thunder...

134
00:09:02,282 --> 00:09:03,890
the breathing fundamentals.

135
00:09:05,374 --> 00:09:08,612
All other techniques branched off from those five,

136
00:09:08,932 --> 00:09:10,984
like how Mist is a branch of Wind.

137
00:09:12,756 --> 00:09:13,616
Mizoguchi...

138
00:09:14,350 --> 00:09:15,721
what color is your sword?

139
00:09:15,861 --> 00:09:20,130
Huh? My name is Kamado, and my sword is black.

140
00:09:20,570 --> 00:09:21,577
Is it, now?

141
00:09:22,050 --> 00:09:24,771
How unfortunate!

142
00:09:25,138 --> 00:09:26,457
Why do you say that?

143
00:09:27,044 --> 00:09:30,028
I've yet to see one with a black sword become a Hashira.

144
00:09:30,619 --> 00:09:34,175
Also, I hear they have no idea what style to master.

145
00:09:36,436 --> 00:09:38,738
There is no need for you to worry!

146
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:40,344
I can train you!

147
00:09:40,611 --> 00:09:41,946
Maybe later.

148
00:09:42,066 --> 00:09:44,210
And just how did you get so big again?!

149
00:09:51,901 --> 00:09:52,927
<i>He's odd...</i>

150
00:09:53,507 --> 00:09:55,118
<i>but he's got a good heart.</i>

151
00:09:55,671 --> 00:09:58,481
<i>And I can smell he has a strong sense of justice.</i>

152
00:10:01,132 --> 00:10:03,720
This is great! It's going so fast!

153
00:10:05,637 --> 00:10:06,811
Get back in here!

154
00:10:06,836 --> 00:10:07,358
That's dangerous!

155
00:10:07,382 --> 00:10:08,389
Let me at 'em!

156
00:10:08,529 --> 00:10:11,083
I wanna race to see who's faster on foot!

157
00:10:12,282 --> 00:10:14,101
You can't be that stupid, can you?!

158
00:10:14,147 --> 00:10:15,087
I wouldn't.

159
00:10:15,847 --> 00:10:17,855
Who knows when a demon might appear?

160
00:10:18,707 --> 00:10:19,242
Wha?

161
00:10:22,096 --> 00:10:24,764
Wait. Demons show up on this train?

162
00:10:25,819 --> 00:10:26,513
They do!

163
00:10:26,902 --> 00:10:29,456
Seriously?! No!

164
00:10:29,481 --> 00:10:31,236
I thought we were meeting up with them,

165
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:32,709
not trapped with them!

166
00:10:34,461 --> 00:10:36,496
I'm getting off this train!

167
00:10:36,876 --> 00:10:41,106
Over 40 people have gone missing from
this train in a short period of time.

168
00:10:42,021 --> 00:10:43,709
We sent in several swordsmen.

169
00:10:43,974 --> 00:10:45,682
However, they have all vanished,

170
00:10:46,682 --> 00:10:48,746
and that is the reason I'm here.

171
00:10:54,905 --> 00:10:56,446
Oh, I see now.

172
00:10:56,471 --> 00:10:59,492
Excuse me. This is my stop. I'm getting off!

173
00:11:07,510 --> 00:11:08,329
May I...

174
00:11:08,783 --> 00:11:09,773
see your...

175
00:11:10,325 --> 00:11:12,191
tickets, please?

176
00:11:13,135 --> 00:11:14,514
What's happening?

177
00:11:14,794 --> 00:11:15,747
That man there,

178
00:11:15,926 --> 00:11:18,234
he is going to check that your ticket is valid.

179
00:11:29,762 --> 00:11:30,402
Here.

180
00:11:55,375 --> 00:11:56,795
<i>That scent...</i>

181
00:11:57,252 --> 00:11:58,353
<i>it's horrible.</i>

182
00:12:00,791 --> 00:12:01,769
Thank you...

183
00:12:02,686 --> 00:12:03,973
very much.

184
00:12:08,516 --> 00:12:09,682
Conductor...

185
00:12:10,222 --> 00:12:11,768
apologies for the sword.

186
00:12:12,408 --> 00:12:13,552
But there is a reason,

187
00:12:13,930 --> 00:12:16,067
so please keep at a safe distance.

188
00:12:36,530 --> 00:12:37,863
What a giant.

189
00:12:38,156 --> 00:12:40,131
Did you use a Blood Demon Art?

190
00:12:40,731 --> 00:12:42,721
It was difficult to detect you.

191
00:12:44,331 --> 00:12:45,451
Know this...

192
00:12:45,537 --> 00:12:48,160
if you bare your fangs at the innocent...

193
00:12:49,667 --> 00:12:52,236
I will see your bone turned to ash...

194
00:12:52,642 --> 00:12:55,399
with my Bright Red Blade of Fire!

195
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:02,273
<i>Flame Breathing.</i>

196
00:13:02,683 --> 00:13:04,251
<i>First Form...</i>

197
00:13:15,278 --> 00:13:16,796
<i>Unknowing Fire!</i>

198
00:13:26,260 --> 00:13:27,180
Amazing.

199
00:13:27,445 --> 00:13:29,445
And with a single slice.

200
00:13:33,021 --> 00:13:34,508
There's still one more.

201
00:13:35,048 --> 00:13:35,766
Come with me.

202
00:13:36,452 --> 00:13:37,079
Huh?

203
00:13:37,973 --> 00:13:39,626
All right!

204
00:13:40,649 --> 00:13:43,111
Hey, don't leave me here!

205
00:14:02,912 --> 00:14:05,057
You will not lay a finger on that man!

206
00:14:10,369 --> 00:14:12,056
Let me make this clear.

207
00:14:12,275 --> 00:14:14,817
Your opponent stands before you now.

208
00:14:15,098 --> 00:14:16,673
What is that thing?

209
00:14:16,779 --> 00:14:19,728
Its... Its arms look so freaking long!

210
00:14:19,761 --> 00:14:20,734
All right!

211
00:14:20,888 --> 00:14:22,231
First come, first served!

212
00:14:22,256 --> 00:14:24,794
Hang on! There's still a bystander there!

213
00:14:24,819 --> 00:14:27,335
It won't matter once I kill this!

214
00:14:42,491 --> 00:14:44,848
You'll be safe in the back. Now go!

215
00:14:46,918 --> 00:14:48,727
We don't have to hold back now.

216
00:14:48,752 --> 00:14:50,242
Let's finish this.

217
00:14:59,162 --> 00:15:00,763
<i>Flame Breathing.</i>

218
00:15:01,136 --> 00:15:02,528
<i>Second Form...</i>

219
00:15:06,302 --> 00:15:08,184
<i>Rising Scorching Sun!</i>

220
00:15:30,457 --> 00:15:31,395
Th-That...

221
00:15:32,023 --> 00:15:33,915
was totally cool, Bro!

222
00:15:33,940 --> 00:15:36,108
Talk about genius swordplay!

223
00:15:36,138 --> 00:15:38,246
Please let me tutor under you!

224
00:15:38,303 --> 00:15:39,368
Very well then!

225
00:15:39,461 --> 00:15:41,043
I'll make you a fine swordsman!

226
00:15:41,068 --> 00:15:42,176
Can I join?

227
00:15:42,201 --> 00:15:43,361
Yeah, me, too!

228
00:15:43,514 --> 00:15:45,596
I would be willing to take you all in!

229
00:15:45,789 --> 00:15:48,533
You're awesome, Big Bro!

230
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:49,968
Brother!

231
00:15:50,274 --> 00:15:51,271
Brother!

232
00:15:51,295 --> 00:15:52,371
Bro!

233
00:15:52,396 --> 00:15:55,093
Thanks so much, Big Bro!

234
00:15:57,106 --> 00:15:59,549
Yeah!

235
00:16:35,712 --> 00:16:36,819
As ordered,

236
00:16:37,259 --> 00:16:39,087
I put them all to sleep, sir.

237
00:16:39,807 --> 00:16:43,130
Now please, do the same to me as well, won't you?

238
00:16:43,757 --> 00:16:47,436
Let me be reunited with my dead wife and daughter.

239
00:16:49,231 --> 00:16:52,454
Please, I'm begging you.

240
00:16:54,123 --> 00:16:55,459
Certainly.

241
00:17:00,056 --> 00:17:02,024
You did a fine job.

242
00:17:04,954 --> 00:17:06,554
Now sleep forever.

243
00:17:10,212 --> 00:17:12,642
Dream that you are with your family again.

244
00:17:14,637 --> 00:17:15,581
Pardon me.

245
00:17:17,860 --> 00:17:20,411
What would you like from us?

246
00:17:21,908 --> 00:17:23,914
Those who are sleeping now

247
00:17:24,188 --> 00:17:25,691
will sink even deeper.

248
00:17:26,108 --> 00:17:27,910
Wait here until then.

249
00:17:28,924 --> 00:17:30,921
A few demon hunters...

250
00:17:31,074 --> 00:17:35,178
will sometimes wake unexpectedly from sensing a demon.

251
00:17:36,039 --> 00:17:38,826
So be very careful when you are tying them up

252
00:17:38,851 --> 00:17:41,557
that you do not directly touch their bodies.

253
00:17:42,237 --> 00:17:45,293
I must remain in the first car for the time being.

254
00:17:45,940 --> 00:17:49,112
'Til everything's ready to go, good luck.

255
00:17:50,139 --> 00:17:53,709
You all want peaceful dreams as well, don't you?

256
00:17:53,856 --> 00:17:54,662
Yes.

257
00:18:51,539 --> 00:18:53,489
<i>What's going on? What happened?</i>

258
00:19:00,763 --> 00:19:01,743
<i>Calm down.</i>

259
00:19:01,924 --> 00:19:03,303
<i>Just calm down.</i>

260
00:19:04,881 --> 00:19:06,297
<i>Slow your breathing.</i>

261
00:19:16,048 --> 00:19:16,453
Huh?

262
00:19:16,868 --> 00:19:17,454
Look!

263
00:19:18,001 --> 00:19:19,490
Brother's back home!

264
00:19:19,994 --> 00:19:21,864
Welcome home, Tanjiro!

265
00:19:22,237 --> 00:19:23,652
You sell the charcoal?

266
00:19:41,430 --> 00:19:42,662
Hey, what's wrong?

267
00:19:56,345 --> 00:19:58,783
Sorry. I'm sorry.

268
00:20:09,007 --> 00:20:11,884
To die while in the rapture of a dream,

269
00:20:12,364 --> 00:20:14,378
a blessing indeed.

270
00:20:15,103 --> 00:20:18,994
It doesn't matter how powerful a demon hunter you are.

271
00:20:19,627 --> 00:20:24,077
The spark that drives these beings comes from the heart,

272
00:20:24,776 --> 00:20:26,896
the human spirit.

273
00:20:27,980 --> 00:20:31,625
All you have to do is stamp out their spiritual core.

274
00:20:31,985 --> 00:20:34,136
You can kill them just like that.

275
00:20:34,449 --> 00:20:37,266
All human hearts work in the same fashion.

276
00:20:38,073 --> 00:20:40,131
Like a delicate glasswork,

277
00:20:40,403 --> 00:20:43,272
they're so pitifully fragile and weak.

278
00:20:45,872 --> 00:20:48,838
We have to tie up their wrists, is that right?

279
00:20:49,310 --> 00:20:52,531
Yeah, and don't forget what he warned us about.

280
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,908
Take in a deep, slow breath.

281
00:21:05,234 --> 00:21:07,254
Then start counting upwards.

282
00:21:09,325 --> 00:21:11,371
<i>Do that, and you'll fall asleep.</i>

283
00:21:12,843 --> 00:21:13,452
<i>One...</i>

284
00:21:14,636 --> 00:21:15,116
<i>two...</i>

285
00:21:16,123 --> 00:21:16,749
<i>three...</i>

286
00:21:17,903 --> 00:21:18,503
<i>four...</i>

287
00:21:19,966 --> 00:21:20,593
<i>five...</i>

288
00:21:21,865 --> 00:21:22,693
<i>six...</i>

289
00:21:28,171 --> 00:21:30,834
And then he suddenly burst into tears.

290
00:21:30,921 --> 00:21:32,524
We were pretty surprised.

291
00:21:32,784 --> 00:21:34,415
What an odd duck!

292
00:21:35,895 --> 00:21:39,485
Well, maybe you're just exhausted is all.

293
00:21:39,692 --> 00:21:42,193
Don't worry about me. I'll be fine.

294
00:21:45,751 --> 00:21:47,962
You don't have a fever, do you, dear?

295
00:21:48,789 --> 00:21:50,050
Don't push yourself.

296
00:21:50,657 --> 00:21:52,112
Just rest for today.

297
00:21:52,892 --> 00:21:54,310
Really, I'm all right.

298
00:21:54,540 --> 00:21:55,571
Are you sure?

299
00:21:56,564 --> 00:21:58,774
Hey! Come back with that!

300
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:00,667
Whoa!

301
00:22:00,869 --> 00:22:03,211
Just what do you think you're doing, huh?

302
00:22:04,071 --> 00:22:04,647
Come on!

303
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:06,554
You stop that right now!

304
00:22:06,714 --> 00:22:08,136
Are you listening?!

305
00:22:08,476 --> 00:22:09,285
I guess...

306
00:22:09,697 --> 00:22:12,222
I was having a bad dream or something earlier.

307
00:22:16,108 --> 00:22:17,501
Hush, my child.

308
00:22:17,765 --> 00:22:19,926
Sleep well, my child.

309
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:23,310
Sleep soundly. Forget to breathe.

310
00:22:23,822 --> 00:22:26,337
Should a demon appear, sleep.

311
00:22:27,677 --> 00:22:30,774
Even inside its stomach, sleep.

312
00:22:32,007 --> 00:22:33,617
Oh, that's delightful.

313
00:22:34,057 --> 00:22:36,848
you must be having such wonderful dreams.

314
00:22:40,942 --> 00:22:42,276
Fall deeper...

315
00:22:43,052 --> 00:22:44,549
and deeper still...

316
00:22:45,159 --> 00:22:46,946
into your dream.

317
00:22:53,248 --> 00:22:54,962
Continue to slumber...

318
00:22:56,518 --> 00:22:57,424
and...

319
00:22:58,574 --> 00:23:00,923
you shall never be roused again.

320
00:23:10,725 --> 00:23:12,082
Here. Let me show you!

321
00:23:12,475 --> 00:23:14,166
These peaches are delicious!

322
00:23:14,659 --> 00:23:16,378
And with all the white clover in bloom,

323
00:23:16,403 --> 00:23:18,198
I can make you a ring of flowers.

324
00:23:19,217 --> 00:23:20,992
I'm pretty good at it. You'll see.

325
00:23:21,723 --> 00:23:22,674
Come on, Nezuko.

326
00:23:23,042 --> 00:23:25,518
Yeah! Make a lot, okay?

327
00:23:26,340 --> 00:23:27,488
I'd love that!

328
00:23:31,748 --> 00:23:33,904
Yahoo!

329
00:23:35,114 --> 00:23:37,939
We have to cross a river, but don't worry. It's shallow.

330
00:23:38,613 --> 00:23:39,565
River?

331
00:23:41,781 --> 00:23:43,477
But I can't swim at all.

332
00:23:44,156 --> 00:23:46,298
Zenitsu, what do I do?

333
00:23:47,717 --> 00:23:51,734
It's fine! I'll just carry
you on my back and jump over it!

334
00:23:52,263 --> 00:23:54,195
Not even your toes will get wet.

335
00:23:55,833 --> 00:23:56,735
Hyah!

336
00:23:56,820 --> 00:23:59,604
Just leave it all to me!

337
00:24:00,603 --> 00:24:02,511
Here we go!

338
00:24:17,479 --> 00:24:19,578
Survey Team! Survey Team!

339
00:24:19,698 --> 00:24:21,610
We are the Cave Survey Team!

340
00:24:21,664 --> 00:24:23,536
Survey Team! Survey Team!

341
00:24:23,583 --> 00:24:25,365
We are the Cave Survey Team!

342
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:26,783
Survey Team! Survey Team!

343
00:24:26,807 --> 00:24:27,615
Hey, Boss!

344
00:24:27,708 --> 00:24:28,734
Wait, Boss!

345
00:24:29,470 --> 00:24:30,310
What is it...

346
00:24:30,356 --> 00:24:32,526
Underling One and Underling Two?

347
00:24:32,926 --> 00:24:33,983
Over there!

348
00:24:34,037 --> 00:24:37,099
I smell the master of this cave, clear as trash!

349
00:24:37,632 --> 00:24:40,424
And its snoring doesn't squeak by me!

350
00:24:45,931 --> 00:24:49,817
There he is, all right! Underlings, go get him!

351
00:24:50,164 --> 00:24:51,745
You got it, Boss man!

352
00:24:52,265 --> 00:24:53,042
Hey, you!

353
00:24:53,352 --> 00:24:55,337
Don't fall behind, Underling Three!

354
00:24:55,362 --> 00:24:57,263
Come on. Look!

355
00:24:57,288 --> 00:24:59,410
I'll give you these sparkly acorns.

356
00:24:59,563 --> 00:25:01,549
Let's go!

357
00:25:01,624 --> 00:25:03,206
Yeah!

358
00:25:30,110 --> 00:25:30,516
Hmm?

359
00:25:32,061 --> 00:25:33,235
<i>Why am I here?</i>

360
00:25:37,776 --> 00:25:40,646
<i>Right. To report to my father</i>

361
00:25:41,203 --> 00:25:42,753
<i>about becoming a Hashira.</i>

362
00:26:03,733 --> 00:26:06,195
So what if you've become a Hashira?

363
00:26:11,004 --> 00:26:13,205
Worthless. It means nothing.

364
00:26:14,142 --> 00:26:16,234
You'll still never amount to anything.

365
00:26:18,407 --> 00:26:21,066
Neither you, nor I.

366
00:26:27,209 --> 00:26:29,004
Uh, Brother.

367
00:26:31,307 --> 00:26:33,742
Did your news make Father happy?

368
00:26:34,695 --> 00:26:37,661
I hope when I become a Hashira,

369
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:40,740
that father will acknowledge me as well.

370
00:26:43,767 --> 00:26:45,592
<i>He wasn't always like that.</i>

371
00:26:47,025 --> 00:26:50,006
<i>In fact, he was once a Hashira himself.</i>

372
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,757
<i>He was full of passion.</i>

373
00:26:53,950 --> 00:26:56,786
<i>And then one day, he quit being a swordsman...</i>

374
00:26:58,635 --> 00:26:59,590
<i>just like that.</i>

375
00:27:00,803 --> 00:27:04,724
<i>The man who raised us both with such enthusiasm...</i>

376
00:27:09,271 --> 00:27:10,031
<i>Why?</i>

377
00:27:13,443 --> 00:27:15,652
<i>There's no use in dwelling on this now.</i>

378
00:27:17,319 --> 00:27:20,253
<i>Senjuro has been through even worse.</i>

379
00:27:21,845 --> 00:27:24,934
<i>Our mother died when he was
too young to even remember her...</i>

380
00:27:26,449 --> 00:27:28,201
<i>and the anguish Father's in...</i>

381
00:27:34,010 --> 00:27:35,042
Senjuro...

382
00:27:36,129 --> 00:27:38,470
to be honest, he was not happy.

383
00:27:39,305 --> 00:27:40,971
He said that it meant nothing.

384
00:27:41,978 --> 00:27:45,519
Even so, that will not extinguish my passion.

385
00:27:46,652 --> 00:27:48,869
This flame in my heart burns strong!

386
00:27:49,962 --> 00:27:51,435
I'll never lose faith!

387
00:27:52,381 --> 00:27:53,634
Listen, Senjuro.

388
00:27:56,228 --> 00:27:58,524
Keep this firmly in mind.

389
00:27:59,550 --> 00:28:01,010
You have an older brother...

390
00:28:02,050 --> 00:28:03,929
a brother who believes in you.

391
00:28:04,929 --> 00:28:08,377
Whatever path you take, you're going to become a fine man.

392
00:28:09,591 --> 00:28:12,744
Just keep that burning passion inside your heart.

393
00:28:13,444 --> 00:28:15,290
Let's both do our best,

394
00:28:15,816 --> 00:28:17,543
no matter how lonely it gets.

395
00:28:24,511 --> 00:28:26,131
Everything's set.

396
00:28:26,577 --> 00:28:32,561
The ropes which I created allow one to invade
the dreams of whoever it is you're tethered to.

397
00:28:33,467 --> 00:28:37,946
I always use the utmost caution when I engage in battle.

398
00:28:38,586 --> 00:28:40,945
Hashira or not, once asleep,

399
00:28:40,970 --> 00:28:43,239
you are no different from that of a newborn.

400
00:28:44,299 --> 00:28:49,429
I will enjoy this savory feast after
I have disposed of the demon hunters.

401
00:28:57,989 --> 00:29:00,381
There's no need to tense up quite so much.

402
00:29:01,168 --> 00:29:02,585
Relax your shoulders.

403
00:29:04,434 --> 00:29:05,300
Like this?

404
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:06,515
That's right.

405
00:29:07,882 --> 00:29:08,778
He's here.

406
00:29:09,166 --> 00:29:10,313
Gotta be careful.

407
00:29:11,536 --> 00:29:13,831
<i>I don't want his True Self to see me.</i>

408
00:29:15,302 --> 00:29:18,907
<i>I have to get to the corner of this dream... and quickly!</i>

409
00:29:21,023 --> 00:29:23,976
The dream world I show them isn't infinite.

410
00:29:25,535 --> 00:29:29,021
It's circular, with the dreamer presiding at the center.

411
00:29:30,612 --> 00:29:34,506
The realm of the subconscious
exists just outside the dream,

412
00:29:34,766 --> 00:29:37,099
where you'll find the spiritual core.

413
00:29:38,265 --> 00:29:40,867
That's what you must destroy.

414
00:29:41,287 --> 00:29:43,861
Once you do that, the owner of the dream

415
00:29:44,126 --> 00:29:45,635
will cease to be.

416
00:29:53,766 --> 00:29:54,729
I found it!

417
00:29:55,495 --> 00:29:58,948
Even though I can see further, I can't move beyond this.

418
00:30:02,427 --> 00:30:05,577
<i>I'll destroy his spiritual core as soon as possible.</i>

419
00:30:08,434 --> 00:30:11,891
<i>And then I'll get to experience a happy dream myself!</i>

420
00:30:21,721 --> 00:30:24,321
This is his "realm of the subconscious"?

421
00:30:24,787 --> 00:30:25,989
All this fire...

422
00:30:26,289 --> 00:30:27,429
so hot.

423
00:30:28,382 --> 00:30:29,618
I've gotta hurry.

424
00:30:46,569 --> 00:30:49,196
There it is, the spiritual core.

425
00:30:51,318 --> 00:30:53,539
I've never seen a red one before.

426
00:30:57,826 --> 00:30:59,674
All I have to do now is...

427
00:31:00,109 --> 00:31:01,561
destroy this!

428
00:31:25,416 --> 00:31:30,274
<i>I thought that humans weren't able to
move while they were under a spell like this.</i>

429
00:31:34,570 --> 00:31:37,559
<i>What kind of survival instinct is this?</i>

430
00:31:44,804 --> 00:31:48,978
Tanjiro, I'm going to make your
favorite rice crackers today, all right?

431
00:31:49,371 --> 00:31:50,413
Really?!

432
00:31:50,793 --> 00:31:53,763
Yes. Let me break up some old rice cakes.

433
00:31:54,107 --> 00:31:56,598
Hear that, Rokuta? Rice crackers!

434
00:31:56,691 --> 00:31:57,951
No fair!

435
00:31:58,391 --> 00:32:01,310
Brother's not the only one who likes rice crackers.

436
00:32:01,503 --> 00:32:02,880
I want some, too!

437
00:32:02,959 --> 00:32:03,959
Me, three!

438
00:32:04,107 --> 00:32:06,697
Well, let's eat them together then!

439
00:32:07,077 --> 00:32:08,709
Can you all get the grill ready?

440
00:32:08,734 --> 00:32:09,500
Yeah!

441
00:32:10,527 --> 00:32:12,390
I'll crush them up in the grinding bowl!

442
00:32:12,742 --> 00:32:15,578
Okay, then I'll be in charge of flipping them over!

443
00:32:15,603 --> 00:32:16,265
I'll help!

444
00:32:16,903 --> 00:32:19,011
Then I'll be in charge of eating them!

445
00:32:19,608 --> 00:32:20,868
No fair!

446
00:32:37,447 --> 00:32:38,834
Nezuko, ready?

447
00:32:48,270 --> 00:32:49,549
What am I saying?

448
00:32:52,929 --> 00:32:53,868
I'm back!

449
00:32:56,020 --> 00:32:57,574
Welcome home, Tanjiro.

450
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,835
It's good to be home.

451
00:33:02,071 --> 00:33:03,490
Welcome home, Brother.

452
00:33:07,133 --> 00:33:08,552
Eh? Where's Nezuko?

453
00:33:09,155 --> 00:33:12,023
She went up the mountain to go pick vegetables.

454
00:33:12,156 --> 00:33:14,264
Huh? In broad daylight?

455
00:33:15,117 --> 00:33:15,486
Eh?

456
00:33:16,732 --> 00:33:17,832
Is that wrong?

457
00:33:18,412 --> 00:33:18,966
Uh...

458
00:33:19,740 --> 00:33:21,819
well, I guess not.

459
00:33:22,286 --> 00:33:25,369
Tanjiro, could you get the bath ready for me?

460
00:33:25,683 --> 00:33:27,509
I still have more to do here.

461
00:33:31,579 --> 00:33:34,210
I've been saying lots of strange things.

462
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:36,431
Maybe I'm tired.

463
00:33:43,340 --> 00:33:43,986
Huh.

464
00:33:44,187 --> 00:33:45,221
It's gone.

465
00:33:47,121 --> 00:33:49,211
I wonder what that was just now.

466
00:33:49,799 --> 00:33:52,097
Maybe a toolbox?

467
00:33:56,078 --> 00:33:57,454
I must be tired.

468
00:34:01,297 --> 00:34:02,235
<i>Wake up!</i>

469
00:34:05,634 --> 00:34:06,535
<i>Wake up!</i>

470
00:34:10,654 --> 00:34:13,202
<i>We're in danger! You've gotta wake up!</i>

471
00:34:13,555 --> 00:34:15,927
<i>All of this, it's all a dream!</i>

472
00:34:16,185 --> 00:34:17,483
<i>Open your eyes!</i>

473
00:34:18,273 --> 00:34:20,546
<i>So that must mean I'm still...</i>

474
00:34:22,165 --> 00:34:23,552
<i>onboard the train!</i>

475
00:34:24,072 --> 00:34:25,587
<i>Wake up, and fight!</i>

476
00:34:25,873 --> 00:34:26,971
<i>You have to!</i>

477
00:34:28,317 --> 00:34:30,659
<i>You have to fight!</i>

478
00:34:35,577 --> 00:34:37,657
Hey, give me your pickled radishes.

479
00:34:37,737 --> 00:34:40,487
Hold it right there, Takeo! That's so not fair!

480
00:34:40,714 --> 00:34:43,681
Why are you always taking food away from Tanjiro, huh?

481
00:34:43,795 --> 00:34:45,036
Mind your own business!

482
00:34:45,061 --> 00:34:46,667
And you just had seconds!

483
00:34:49,793 --> 00:34:50,400
<i>Damn.</i>

484
00:34:50,933 --> 00:34:52,756
<i>I'm still trapped inside this dream.</i>

485
00:34:53,696 --> 00:34:54,716
<i>How do I get out?</i>

486
00:34:55,728 --> 00:34:57,387
<i>Even knowing that it's a dream,</i>

487
00:34:58,444 --> 00:34:59,913
<i>what am I supposed to do?</i>

488
00:35:09,005 --> 00:35:09,756
Hmm?

489
00:35:11,926 --> 00:35:12,576
Hmm.

490
00:35:14,123 --> 00:35:14,730
Hmm?

491
00:35:18,340 --> 00:35:19,624
I've gotta wake up.

492
00:35:24,048 --> 00:35:24,742
Hmm?

493
00:35:58,471 --> 00:35:59,263
Brother!

494
00:35:59,399 --> 00:36:00,627
What do we do?!

495
00:36:00,776 --> 00:36:01,654
Tanjiro!

496
00:36:04,659 --> 00:36:06,257
<i>This scent of blood...</i>

497
00:36:07,030 --> 00:36:07,891
<i>I know it.</i>

498
00:36:09,792 --> 00:36:10,780
<i>Nezuko.</i>

499
00:36:11,447 --> 00:36:12,453
<i>It's Nezuko!</i>

500
00:36:17,600 --> 00:36:19,637
<i>My uniform, my sword.</i>

501
00:36:20,291 --> 00:36:21,408
<i>I'm waking up.</i>

502
00:36:22,245 --> 00:36:25,240
<i>I can feel it, little by little.</i>

503
00:36:26,160 --> 00:36:27,222
What happened?

504
00:36:27,415 --> 00:36:29,166
We were really scared there.

505
00:36:29,405 --> 00:36:30,659
You all right?

506
00:36:31,734 --> 00:36:33,880
Sorry, everyone.

507
00:36:39,628 --> 00:36:40,869
<i>There's no other choice.</i>

508
00:36:43,075 --> 00:36:44,075
I have to go.

509
00:36:45,043 --> 00:36:45,796
Brother!

510
00:36:45,963 --> 00:36:46,537
Wait!

511
00:36:46,843 --> 00:36:48,209
Where are you going?

512
00:36:53,862 --> 00:36:56,644
<i>If the demon who's showing me this dream is nearby,</i>

513
00:36:57,346 --> 00:36:59,197
<i>I have to defeat it quickly!</i>

514
00:37:01,088 --> 00:37:02,356
<i>Time's running out.</i>

515
00:37:02,844 --> 00:37:03,745
<i>Where is it?</i>

516
00:37:06,390 --> 00:37:08,194
Where are you running off to?

517
00:37:15,948 --> 00:37:18,663
I picked lots of vegetables from the mountain.

518
00:37:23,423 --> 00:37:25,591
He went this way, Mom! Hurry! Come on!

519
00:37:25,804 --> 00:37:28,504
Brother just suddenly bust into flames!

520
00:37:31,219 --> 00:37:32,187
What happened?

521
00:37:33,014 --> 00:37:35,317
Tanjiro, are you all right?

522
00:37:36,198 --> 00:37:37,217
Tanjiro.

523
00:37:44,648 --> 00:37:46,001
What's the matter, dear?

524
00:37:46,322 --> 00:37:48,136
And why are you dressed like that?

525
00:37:57,259 --> 00:37:58,026
I wish...

526
00:37:59,813 --> 00:38:02,561
I wish I could stay. I do.

527
00:38:06,428 --> 00:38:08,188
<i>I'd live with you all forever.</i>

528
00:38:09,932 --> 00:38:11,529
<i>Just like how it should have been...</i>

529
00:38:12,141 --> 00:38:13,375
<i>from the very beginning...</i>

530
00:38:14,976 --> 00:38:15,877
<i>right here.</i>

531
00:38:17,834 --> 00:38:19,674
<i>If things had been as they should have,</i>

532
00:38:20,276 --> 00:38:21,660
<i>you'd all be alive.</i>

533
00:38:24,030 --> 00:38:26,609
<i>And Nezuko would be able to be in the sunlight,</i>

534
00:38:27,509 --> 00:38:28,783
<i>under the blue sky.</i>

535
00:38:31,714 --> 00:38:32,941
<i>That's how it'd be...</i>

536
00:38:33,684 --> 00:38:35,085
<i>how it should have been.</i>

537
00:38:36,375 --> 00:38:38,919
<i>I would still be here making charcoal.</i>

538
00:38:39,919 --> 00:38:42,463
<i>I would have never laid a hand on a sword.</i>

539
00:38:46,501 --> 00:38:47,468
<i>If only...</i>

540
00:38:48,841 --> 00:38:50,929
<i>if only it could have stayed that way.</i>

541
00:39:04,678 --> 00:39:05,565
<i>But now...</i>

542
00:39:06,158 --> 00:39:07,282
<i>they're all gone.</i>

543
00:39:07,943 --> 00:39:09,670
<i>I can never go back!</i>

544
00:39:13,244 --> 00:39:14,718
Tanjiro!

545
00:39:14,977 --> 00:39:17,750
Please don't leave us behind!

546
00:39:24,233 --> 00:39:27,564
