796
00:57:52,166 --> 00:57:55,013
What a lovely expression on your face,

797
00:57:55,238 --> 00:57:57,708
one that I have been longing to see.

798
00:57:59,735 --> 00:58:02,612
You're wondering why I'm still alive,

799
00:58:02,752 --> 00:58:04,811
even after you decapitated me.

800
00:58:05,504 --> 00:58:09,452
Well, I'll tell you, since I'm feeling so ecstatic.

801
00:58:09,933 --> 00:58:14,337
I'll try to use small words so even you can understand it.

802
00:58:16,134 --> 00:58:19,826
It's because that wasn't actually my true self.

803
00:58:20,666 --> 00:58:23,412
The same can be said about what's before you.

804
00:58:23,525 --> 00:58:27,369
It may look like my head, but that is not the case.

805
00:58:27,795 --> 00:58:30,975
While you were sleeping like a helpless little baby,

806
00:58:31,068 --> 00:58:35,566
I fused my being with this entire train!

807
00:58:36,146 --> 00:58:39,765
Every inch of it has become my blood, my flesh,

808
00:58:39,918 --> 00:58:42,511
right down to my bones!

809
00:58:43,751 --> 00:58:45,490
The look in your eye.

810
00:58:45,709 --> 00:58:47,707
You're starting to understand.

811
00:58:47,994 --> 00:58:54,243
For, you see, the more than 200 passengers
on this train... or should I say hostages...

812
00:58:54,342 --> 00:58:56,412
will soon become part of my body.

813
00:58:59,857 --> 00:59:02,285
Do you think you can protect them?

814
00:59:02,497 --> 00:59:06,906
Can you alone prevent me from
feasting on all the tasty human flesh

815
00:59:06,931 --> 00:59:09,876
that's been packed from stem to stern?

816
00:59:10,656 --> 00:59:13,808
Or will my appetite be satiated in full?

817
00:59:20,830 --> 00:59:23,058
<i>Damn it. What do I do?</i>

818
00:59:24,085 --> 00:59:26,147
<i>I can only protect two cars at most.</i>

819
00:59:27,337 --> 00:59:29,230
<i>Any more is too much for me to handle.</i>

820
00:59:30,556 --> 00:59:33,890
Rengoku! Zenitsu! Inosuke!

821
00:59:34,347 --> 00:59:36,045
I really need your help!

822
00:59:36,246 --> 00:59:38,285
Please wake up! I'm begging you!

823
00:59:39,286 --> 00:59:43,552
Nezuko! I'm trusting you to
look after the other passengers!

824
00:59:52,880 --> 00:59:55,068
Comin' through!

825
00:59:55,093 --> 00:59:55,835
All right,

826
00:59:55,860 --> 00:59:57,335
listen up, my minions!

827
00:59:57,382 --> 00:59:58,723
Follow me!

828
00:59:58,984 --> 01:00:00,637
Keep those eyes open...

829
01:00:01,492 --> 01:00:03,607
and keep them forward!

830
01:00:03,632 --> 01:00:07,256
'Cause Lord Inosuke is comin' through!

831
01:00:07,796 --> 01:00:11,319
Inosuke, the whole train has turned into a demon!

832
01:00:11,659 --> 01:00:13,442
There's nowhere on it that's safe!

833
01:00:13,701 --> 01:00:16,105
So we have to protect the passengers!

834
01:00:16,131 --> 01:00:19,802
I repeat! This entire train is a demon!

835
01:00:19,835 --> 01:00:20,550
Huh?

836
01:00:20,948 --> 01:00:22,410
What do you know?

837
01:00:22,543 --> 01:00:24,214
I was right all along!

838
01:00:24,647 --> 01:00:28,844
Talk about having absolute
killer instincts as a leader, huh?

839
01:00:33,109 --> 01:00:35,040
Beast Breathing.

840
01:00:35,239 --> 01:00:39,252
Fifth Fang, Crazy Cutting!

841
01:00:43,433 --> 01:00:46,751
I'll be sure to save every last one of you!

842
01:00:46,896 --> 01:00:53,197
As thanks, it's only fair you should fall
onto one knee and worship me as your savior!

843
01:00:53,530 --> 01:00:58,180
Lord Inosuke Hashibira, I'm comin' through!

844
01:00:58,994 --> 01:01:00,663
I have to save the others.

845
01:01:01,714 --> 01:01:03,907
If Inosuke's handling those cars,

846
01:01:04,185 --> 01:01:05,587
I should go on ahead.

847
01:01:30,051 --> 01:01:31,813
It's gotten this far already?

848
01:01:35,968 --> 01:01:37,225
<i>Water Breathing.</i>

849
01:01:37,250 --> 01:01:40,603
<i>First Form, Water Surface Slash!</i>

850
01:01:43,641 --> 01:01:46,861
<i>No good. This is never going to end.</i>

851
01:01:47,403 --> 01:01:48,841
<i>How do I fend it off?!</i>

852
01:01:55,363 --> 01:01:58,253
<i>I feel you scurrying around inside me</i>

853
01:01:58,545 --> 01:02:00,961
<i>like a loathsome parasite.</i>

854
01:02:01,701 --> 01:02:05,021
<i>Flail all you want, but I'll just keep regenerating.</i>

855
01:02:05,302 --> 01:02:09,230
<i>And then once all of your energy is wasted,</i>

856
01:02:09,656 --> 01:02:12,953
<i>I'm going to enjoy dining on the passengers here</i>

857
01:02:13,262 --> 01:02:15,650
<i>like an exquisite banquet.</i>

858
01:03:27,369 --> 01:03:29,028
<i>Thunder Breathing.</i>

859
01:03:29,441 --> 01:03:30,699
<i>First Form...</i>

860
01:03:31,665 --> 01:03:33,476
<i>Thunderclap and Flash.</i>

861
01:03:37,176 --> 01:03:38,180
<i>Sixfold.</i>

862
01:03:38,849 --> 01:03:40,020
Nezuko...

863
01:03:40,884 --> 01:03:42,539
I will protect you.

864
01:03:45,203 --> 01:03:46,897
Protect you.

865
01:03:47,830 --> 01:03:48,863
I...

866
01:03:51,389 --> 01:03:52,829
Hmm?

867
01:03:52,929 --> 01:03:54,731
<i>That sounded like thunder.</i>

868
01:03:54,803 --> 01:03:56,409
<i>Did it come from back there?</i>

869
01:03:56,842 --> 01:03:58,149
<i>What's happening?</i>

870
01:03:58,848 --> 01:04:00,503
<i>Is Zenitsu awake now?</i>

871
01:04:00,529 --> 01:04:02,149
<i>What about Mr. Rengoku...</i>

872
01:04:02,765 --> 01:04:03,815
<i>and Nezuko!</i>

873
01:04:09,558 --> 01:04:11,807
<i>It's all I can do to protect the ones here.</i>

874
01:04:13,411 --> 01:04:15,990
<i>What should I do? We can't fight together.</i>

875
01:04:16,983 --> 01:04:19,058
<i>Are the passengers in the back all right?</i>

876
01:04:19,904 --> 01:04:20,861
<i>Damn it!</i>

877
01:04:20,886 --> 01:04:22,396
<i>There's no room to move here.</i>

878
01:04:23,813 --> 01:04:25,575
<i>It's hard to swing my sword.</i>

879
01:04:30,370 --> 01:04:30,950
Hmm.

880
01:04:32,053 --> 01:04:35,478
It would appear that a lot
has gone on since I was napping.

881
01:04:36,391 --> 01:04:38,850
What an ugly mess.

882
01:04:39,300 --> 01:04:41,643
If the other Hashira were here...

883
01:04:43,026 --> 01:04:45,083
to see what I let happen...

884
01:04:46,796 --> 01:04:48,029
I'd be ashamed!

885
01:04:55,502 --> 01:04:56,657
What happened?

886
01:05:02,472 --> 01:05:05,080
<i>What was that? Did a demon attack?</i>

887
01:05:08,088 --> 01:05:09,174
Young Kamado!

888
01:05:10,978 --> 01:05:12,397
Mr. Rengoku!

889
01:05:12,837 --> 01:05:15,568
I was quite thorough with my strikes on the way here,

890
01:05:15,657 --> 01:05:18,631
so it should take the demon a while to recuperate,

891
01:05:19,364 --> 01:05:21,192
but there's still no time to waste.

892
01:05:21,435 --> 01:05:22,135
Right!

893
01:05:22,542 --> 01:05:24,512
This train has eight cars.

894
01:05:24,958 --> 01:05:26,789
I will protect the rear five.

895
01:05:27,317 --> 01:05:30,710
The other three will be handled by
your sister and that boy in yellow.

896
01:05:31,494 --> 01:05:36,562
During all this, you will go with the
boar-headed lad and search for the demon's head.

897
01:05:37,182 --> 01:05:38,134
Its head?

898
01:05:38,492 --> 01:05:39,924
But, sir, how can we...

899
01:05:39,949 --> 01:05:41,576
Kill something without a head?

900
01:05:41,716 --> 01:05:43,622
It's still a demon. It has one.

901
01:05:44,042 --> 01:05:45,712
I will search for it as well.

902
01:05:46,048 --> 01:05:47,731
I hope you're fired up.

903
01:05:52,096 --> 01:05:53,703
<i>It's like he just disappeared.</i>

904
01:05:53,944 --> 01:05:56,109
<i>Is that what made the train shake earlier?</i>

905
01:05:58,266 --> 01:06:00,739
<i>His tactical mind is just as quick, too.</i>

906
01:06:01,276 --> 01:06:02,982
<i>Handling five cars?</i>

907
01:06:04,462 --> 01:06:06,313
<i>This is no time to get distracted.</i>

908
01:06:06,566 --> 01:06:07,985
<i>You have to get a move on.</i>

909
01:06:08,625 --> 01:06:10,802
<i>The demon's scent is getting stronger by the moment.</i>

910
01:06:10,900 --> 01:06:11,969
<i>Let's go!</i>

911
01:06:13,840 --> 01:06:16,028
Inosuke, where are you?!

912
01:06:16,781 --> 01:06:18,441
Shut up, or I'll end you!

913
01:06:18,534 --> 01:06:19,309
Up there?

914
01:06:19,778 --> 01:06:24,265
I already got my marching orders from Mr. Bug Eyes!

915
01:06:24,512 --> 01:06:26,814
Even with him bossing me around, though...

916
01:06:27,420 --> 01:06:30,137
he... he was really cool!

917
01:06:30,509 --> 01:06:33,395
And for some reason, that pisses me off!

918
01:06:33,654 --> 01:06:37,178
Inosuke, keep an eye on the three cars in the front!

919
01:06:37,239 --> 01:06:38,644
You don't have to tell me!

920
01:06:38,756 --> 01:06:41,364
Besides, using my awesome Seventh Form,

921
01:06:41,570 --> 01:06:44,148
I've already found what it is we're looking for,

922
01:06:44,301 --> 01:06:46,135
the Master's weak spot!

923
01:06:46,665 --> 01:06:49,473
You found it? So it is up front then?

924
01:06:49,697 --> 01:06:50,873
It sure is.

925
01:06:50,961 --> 01:06:53,819
And that area creeps me out even more.

926
01:06:54,579 --> 01:06:57,357
<i>I can't pick up on the scent because of the strong winds,</i>

927
01:06:57,517 --> 01:06:59,437
<i>but I trust Inosuke's senses.</i>

928
01:07:00,556 --> 01:07:02,647
Is it around where the coal's loaded?

929
01:07:02,813 --> 01:07:03,840
That's right!

930
01:07:04,014 --> 01:07:04,659
Got it!

931
01:07:05,240 --> 01:07:06,761
Inosuke, ready?

932
01:07:07,322 --> 01:07:08,208
Let's go!

933
01:07:20,528 --> 01:07:22,183
This is it, huh?

934
01:07:26,329 --> 01:07:27,305
All right!

935
01:07:34,736 --> 01:07:35,976
Inosuke!

936
01:07:36,382 --> 01:07:39,038
What the hell's going on over here, huh?

937
01:07:39,384 --> 01:07:41,373
This seems pretty suspicious.

938
01:07:41,573 --> 01:07:43,274
Just who the hell are you?

939
01:07:43,783 --> 01:07:45,069
Le-Leave this area!

940
01:07:45,268 --> 01:07:46,891
It's there, isn't it,

941
01:07:47,227 --> 01:07:48,631
the weak spot?

942
01:07:48,704 --> 01:07:50,152
It's mine!

943
01:07:53,109 --> 01:07:54,029
Eep!

944
01:07:55,169 --> 01:07:56,315
Aw, crap!

945
01:07:56,415 --> 01:07:59,014
Keep away from me, you foul beast!

946
01:08:01,047 --> 01:08:02,931
How many hands you got?!

947
01:08:03,157 --> 01:08:04,271
Not good.

948
01:08:07,241 --> 01:08:08,371
<i>Water Breathing.</i>

949
01:08:08,524 --> 01:08:11,295
<i>Sixth Form, Whirlpool!</i>

950
01:08:19,308 --> 01:08:20,803
Are you all right, Inosuke?

951
01:08:21,136 --> 01:08:23,405
It's not like you came to my rescue, okay!

952
01:08:23,546 --> 01:08:24,425
I'm sorry!

953
01:08:27,235 --> 01:08:28,049
<i>It's here.</i>

954
01:08:29,590 --> 01:08:30,581
<i>Right below.</i>

955
01:08:31,347 --> 01:08:32,580
<i>I can smell it.</i>

956
01:08:33,054 --> 01:08:34,585
<i>There's no doubt in my mind.</i>

957
01:08:35,026 --> 01:08:37,648
Inosuke, the demon's head is under here!

958
01:08:37,835 --> 01:08:39,217
Don't order me around!

959
01:08:39,297 --> 01:08:40,683
I'm the leader, remember?!

960
01:08:40,856 --> 01:08:41,833
Then what's next?

961
01:08:41,989 --> 01:08:43,362
Just you watch.

962
01:08:43,675 --> 01:08:46,674
This is Beast Breathing, Second Fang!

963
01:08:48,023 --> 01:08:49,201
Slice!

964
01:08:56,258 --> 01:08:57,066
This is...

965
01:08:57,751 --> 01:08:59,011
his neck bone.

966
01:08:59,937 --> 01:09:00,848
<i>Water Breathing!</i>

967
01:09:00,907 --> 01:09:01,998
<i>Eighth Form...</i>

968
01:09:02,683 --> 01:09:04,431
<i>Waterfall Basin!</i>

969
01:09:08,250 --> 01:09:09,250
<i>It deflected.</i>

970
01:09:25,787 --> 01:09:28,648
<i>It's healing so fast, the wound's already closed up.</i>

971
01:09:29,996 --> 01:09:33,292
<i>Just exposing the bone took
everything I could muster, too.</i>

972
01:09:34,889 --> 01:09:36,242
<i>I have to sever it.</i>

973
01:09:36,928 --> 01:09:40,350
Inosuke, let's synchronize our attacks!

974
01:09:40,810 --> 01:09:42,434
You'll slash at the flesh,

975
01:09:42,580 --> 01:09:44,839
which will allow me to strike at the bone!

976
01:09:45,198 --> 01:09:46,374
You wanna know somethin'?

977
01:09:46,674 --> 01:09:47,965
That's not half-bad!

978
01:09:48,165 --> 01:09:49,014
Good thinkin'!

979
01:09:49,278 --> 01:09:50,067
Thank you!

980
01:09:51,754 --> 01:09:52,846
Let's do it.

981
01:10:01,331 --> 01:10:03,547
Eyes of Forced Unconscious Sleep.

982
01:10:04,054 --> 01:10:05,335
Dream.

983
01:10:05,886 --> 01:10:07,417
<i>A Blood Demon Art!</i>

984
01:10:08,007 --> 01:10:08,994
<i>He got me.</i>

985
01:10:09,151 --> 01:10:10,487
<i>I'm falling asleep.</i>

986
01:10:11,560 --> 01:10:14,768
Inosuke, in your dream, slice your own neck!

987
01:10:15,044 --> 01:10:16,411
It'll wake you up!

988
01:10:21,137 --> 01:10:22,103
<i>It's all right.</i>

989
01:10:22,405 --> 01:10:24,173
<i>I'm still able to break the spell.</i>

990
01:10:25,538 --> 01:10:30,124
<i>Idiot. When you wake up, keep your eyes
closed, or you'll just fall asleep again.</i>

991
01:10:31,921 --> 01:10:33,529
<i>Okay, I'm awake.</i>

992
01:10:38,437 --> 01:10:40,978
<i>Damn! The moment I wake up,</i>

993
01:10:41,011 --> 01:10:44,171
<i>I can't help but look directly
into one of those demon eyes.</i>

994
01:10:44,831 --> 01:10:46,852
<i>I've got to make sure when I wake up</i>

995
01:10:47,228 --> 01:10:48,983
<i>that I keep my eyes shut!</i>

996
01:10:50,951 --> 01:10:51,698
<i>Again!</i>

997
01:10:52,312 --> 01:10:53,026
<i>Wake up!</i>

998
01:10:53,439 --> 01:10:54,430
<i>Wake up!</i>

999
01:10:55,323 --> 01:10:56,203
<i>Come on!</i>

1000
01:10:56,616 --> 01:10:57,253
<i>Your neck...</i>

1001
01:10:57,409 --> 01:10:59,608
<i>slash it. Wake up!</i>

1002
01:10:59,947 --> 01:11:01,282
<i>This is a dream!</i>

1003
01:11:03,411 --> 01:11:04,862
<i>There's no time left.</i>

1004
01:11:05,687 --> 01:11:07,311
<i>Wake yourself up!</i>

1005
01:11:11,421 --> 01:11:13,189
You're not dreaming right now.

1006
01:11:13,536 --> 01:11:15,502
Don't go falling for his trickery.

1007
01:11:15,728 --> 01:11:17,963
You wanna look like a damn fool?

1008
01:11:22,304 --> 01:11:25,549
I'm wearing the hide of the Mountain God on my head.

1009
01:11:26,032 --> 01:11:28,777
I bet he's too scared to look me in the eye!

1010
01:11:29,653 --> 01:11:31,753
I'm right, aren't I?!

1011
01:11:32,206 --> 01:11:36,693
<i>Or it's having a hard time
telling which way Inosuke's looking!</i>

1012
01:11:37,176 --> 01:11:38,289
Okay!

1013
01:11:38,596 --> 01:11:40,849
Now we just gotta cut this thing to pieces!

1014
01:11:45,369 --> 01:11:46,393
Inosuke!

1015
01:11:46,728 --> 01:11:49,989
I won't let you take away my chance to dream!

1016
01:11:56,696 --> 01:11:58,233
Did he just stab you?!

1017
01:11:58,406 --> 01:11:59,420
I'm okay.

1018
01:12:02,223 --> 01:12:04,043
Forget about that bastard!

1019
01:12:04,372 --> 01:12:06,667
I can't just leave him to die.

1020
01:12:08,060 --> 01:12:10,348
If we don't chop this thing's head off soon,

1021
01:12:10,395 --> 01:12:11,835
the others won't make it!

1022
01:12:12,028 --> 01:12:12,763
I hear you.

1023
01:12:13,129 --> 01:12:14,067
Let's hurry then.

1024
01:12:31,395 --> 01:12:32,285
Inosuke...

1025
01:12:32,695 --> 01:12:34,250
let's combine our strength.

1026
01:12:34,503 --> 01:12:36,405
Once we've synchronized our breathing,

1027
01:12:36,684 --> 01:12:38,079
we'll attack as one!

1028
01:13:13,658 --> 01:13:16,260
<i>Damn it. If we fall asleep now...</i>

1029
01:13:16,406 --> 01:13:17,793
Not today!

1030
01:13:17,992 --> 01:13:20,092
Come on! Follow the leader!

1031
01:13:20,461 --> 01:13:21,725
Beast Breathing.

1032
01:13:21,871 --> 01:13:23,252
Fourth Form...

1033
01:13:26,160 --> 01:13:27,961
Slice 'n' Dice!

1034
01:13:31,783 --> 01:13:34,367
<i>Father, please guide my blade.</i>

1035
01:13:34,601 --> 01:13:39,571
<i>My chance to sever the bone with one strike... is now!</i>

1036
01:13:39,981 --> 01:13:41,824
<i>Hinokami Kagura!</i>

1037
01:13:43,073 --> 01:13:45,420
<i>Clear Blue Sky!</i>

1038
01:14:06,534 --> 01:14:07,374
Careful!

1039
01:14:07,660 --> 01:14:10,284
The train feels like it's about to tip over!

1040
01:14:10,637 --> 01:14:11,652
Are you all right?

1041
01:14:12,034 --> 01:14:14,835
Am I all right? You're the one still bleeding!

1042
01:14:14,961 --> 01:14:15,903
It's fine.

1043
01:14:16,336 --> 01:14:18,725
Inosuke, protect the passen...

1044
01:14:20,820 --> 01:14:22,047
<i>I can't die.</i>

1045
01:14:22,755 --> 01:14:25,617
<i>I don't want him to live with
his hands stained with blood.</i>

1046
01:14:26,555 --> 01:14:27,952
<i>I have to live.</i>

1047
01:14:30,845 --> 01:14:32,715
<i>I won't let anyone die!</i>

1048
01:14:58,654 --> 01:15:02,106
Santaro! Are you all right?

1049
01:15:04,488 --> 01:15:05,969
Pull yourself together.

1050
01:15:06,083 --> 01:15:08,882
You see me bounce off that demon's flesh just now?

1051
01:15:08,989 --> 01:15:10,480
Wait! What am I saying?!

1052
01:15:11,233 --> 01:15:12,652
You got stabbed, right?

1053
01:15:13,072 --> 01:15:14,553
How's your stomach?

1054
01:15:15,053 --> 01:15:17,588
I'm... I'm all right.

1055
01:15:18,681 --> 01:15:19,702
What about you?

1056
01:15:20,064 --> 01:15:21,721
I've never felt better.

1057
01:15:21,894 --> 01:15:23,129
Not a scratch on me.

1058
01:15:23,886 --> 01:15:24,788
I don't...

1059
01:15:24,974 --> 01:15:26,442
think I can move now.

1060
01:15:28,103 --> 01:15:30,259
Can you go help the others?

1061
01:15:32,014 --> 01:15:33,628
See if anyone's hurt.

1062
01:15:35,287 --> 01:15:36,810
That engineer...

1063
01:15:37,269 --> 01:15:38,567
is he all right?

1064
01:15:40,836 --> 01:15:43,098
Let him die for all I care!

1065
01:15:44,045 --> 01:15:44,945
We can't.

1066
01:15:46,640 --> 01:15:50,075
Did you somehow forget he's the one
who stabbed you in the first place?!

1067
01:15:50,305 --> 01:15:51,976
But if you really wanna know,

1068
01:15:52,054 --> 01:15:54,771
his leg's shattered, and he can't walk anymore.

1069
01:15:54,877 --> 01:15:56,017
Just let him rot!

1070
01:15:56,531 --> 01:15:57,266
Then he's...

1071
01:15:57,478 --> 01:15:59,647
already suffered enough, don't you think?

1072
01:16:00,642 --> 01:16:01,933
Help him, Inosuke.

1073
01:16:04,673 --> 01:16:05,706
For me.

1074
01:16:12,168 --> 01:16:12,669
Fine!

1075
01:16:13,081 --> 01:16:14,537
But only 'cause you asked.

1076
01:16:14,758 --> 01:16:16,202
You are my underling.

1077
01:16:16,422 --> 01:16:18,664
It's the least I can do as a leader!

1078
01:16:18,984 --> 01:16:20,468
And after I've rescued him,

1079
01:16:20,574 --> 01:16:22,851
I'm gonna pluck out all of his hair!

1080
01:16:23,986 --> 01:16:26,984
You really don't have to do that last part.

1081
01:16:31,594 --> 01:16:33,044
<i>It's almost dawn.</i>

1082
01:16:35,224 --> 01:16:37,126
<i>Take control of your breathing.</i>

1083
01:16:38,262 --> 01:16:39,609
<i>Focus your thoughts...</i>

1084
01:16:40,643 --> 01:16:42,992
<i>to save the injured on this train.</i>

1085
01:16:45,080 --> 01:16:46,558
<i>Think of Nezuko...</i>

1086
01:16:46,931 --> 01:16:49,952
<i>Zenitsu, Mr. Rengoku.</i>

1087
01:16:51,205 --> 01:16:53,247
<i>I'm sure the three of them are safe.</i>

1088
01:16:53,628 --> 01:16:55,133
<i>You just have to believe.</i>

1089
01:17:02,153 --> 01:17:04,126
<i>I can't regenerate.</i>

1090
01:17:04,754 --> 01:17:06,093
<i>Have I lost?</i>

1091
01:17:07,432 --> 01:17:09,185
<i>Am I going to die?</i>

1092
01:17:10,362 --> 01:17:11,176
<i>Me?</i>

1093
01:17:12,049 --> 01:17:14,515
<i>Ridiculous. Absurd!</i>

1094
01:17:14,820 --> 01:17:17,216
<i>There was so much more to do!</i>

1095
01:17:17,662 --> 01:17:20,156
<i>I couldn't devour a single human.</i>

1096
01:17:20,462 --> 01:17:25,665
<i>My plan to fuse with the train and
eat everyone was a complete failure!</i>

1097
01:17:25,791 --> 01:17:28,739
<i>And now look at what I've been reduced to.</i>

1098
01:17:29,212 --> 01:17:32,174
<i>After all the preparations I had taken...</i>

1099
01:17:33,205 --> 01:17:34,513
<i>It was him!</i>

1100
01:17:34,754 --> 01:17:36,468
<i>This is his fault!</i>

1101
01:17:37,261 --> 01:17:40,557
<i>Even with all the human hostages I had in my possession,</i>

1102
01:17:40,596 --> 01:17:43,555
<i>I still wasn't able to get the upper hand.</i>

1103
01:17:44,455 --> 01:17:46,830
<i>Is this the power of a Hashira?</i>

1104
01:17:47,261 --> 01:17:49,824
<i>That sun-colored boy was fast, too,</i>

1105
01:17:50,451 --> 01:17:53,238
<i>while still under the effects of my spell.</i>

1106
01:17:53,749 --> 01:17:55,204
<i>And then there's her,</i>

1107
01:17:55,517 --> 01:17:58,598
<i>a demon fighting alongside the Demon Slayers?</i>

1108
01:17:58,894 --> 01:18:00,552
<i>What treachery is this?</i>

1109
01:18:00,689 --> 01:18:03,926
<i>Why does Master Muzan allow her to live?</i>

1110
01:18:05,378 --> 01:18:06,075
<i>Damn it.</i>

1111
01:18:06,246 --> 01:18:07,863
<i>Damn it all.</i>

1112
01:18:08,256 --> 01:18:14,355
<i>It all started going to hell when that
little brat was able to wriggle out of my spell.</i>

1113
01:18:14,822 --> 01:18:16,731
<i>He's to blame for this!</i>

1114
01:18:17,011 --> 01:18:21,031
<i>If I had the strength... I would kill him right now.</i>

1115
01:18:21,555 --> 01:18:23,833
<i>And that beastly boar child,</i>

1116
01:18:23,984 --> 01:18:27,307
<i>I should have killed him when I had the chance, too.</i>

1117
01:18:27,683 --> 01:18:31,698
<i>But I was never able to catch
his gaze and put him back to sleep.</i>

1118
01:18:31,794 --> 01:18:34,309
<i>His instincts were too strong.</i>

1119
01:18:35,632 --> 01:18:37,594
<i>Have I truly lost?</i>

1120
01:18:37,826 --> 01:18:39,241
<i>Is this the end?</i>

1121
01:18:41,046 --> 01:18:45,118
<i>What a terrible, wretched nightmare this is.</i>

1122
01:18:46,331 --> 01:18:50,508
<i>Am I no different from those other
lesser demons who are killed off?</i>

1123
01:18:51,255 --> 01:18:55,991
<i>The Upper Ranks of our kind have
stayed the same for hundreds of years.</i>

1124
01:18:56,358 --> 01:19:00,721
<i>Even Hashira with high body
counts have fallen by their hands.</i>

1125
01:19:01,387 --> 01:19:04,108
<i>Do they have otherworldly powers?</i>

1126
01:19:04,968 --> 01:19:07,507
<i>Even after receiving so much of his blood,</i>

1127
01:19:07,721 --> 01:19:09,478
<i>I couldn't compete with them.</i>

1128
01:19:10,451 --> 01:19:12,799
<i>It's not fair.</i>

1129
01:19:12,837 --> 01:19:15,394
<i>If only I could turn back time.</i>

1130
01:19:15,867 --> 01:19:20,646
<i>Then I could undo this awful, horrible nightmare.</i>

1131
01:19:27,997 --> 01:19:30,812
You've mastered Total Concentration, Constant.

1132
01:19:31,366 --> 01:19:32,769
That's quite impressive.

1133
01:19:33,962 --> 01:19:35,428
Mr. Rengoku.

1134
01:19:36,106 --> 01:19:38,467
You're one step closer to being a Hashira.

1135
01:19:39,334 --> 01:19:41,864
That's one step out of ten thousand, mind you!

1136
01:19:43,619 --> 01:19:44,927
I'll do my best.

1137
01:19:46,149 --> 01:19:47,678
You're bleeding from the gut.

1138
01:19:48,591 --> 01:19:49,794
Regulate your breathing.

1139
01:19:49,881 --> 01:19:51,314
Take full control of it.

1140
01:19:51,895 --> 01:19:54,969
Picture your nerves reaching all though your body.

1141
01:19:55,796 --> 01:19:56,939
Can you see it?

1142
01:19:57,699 --> 01:19:59,101
The torn blood vessel?

1143
01:20:03,212 --> 01:20:04,628
Concentrate harder.

1144
01:20:16,283 --> 01:20:16,963
That's it.

1145
01:20:17,498 --> 01:20:19,220
Now stop the bleeding.

1146
01:20:25,226 --> 01:20:26,126
Focus.

1147
01:20:35,866 --> 01:20:37,967
Good! You succeeded.

1148
01:20:38,607 --> 01:20:42,086
Mastering your breathing, it will open many doors for you.

1149
01:20:42,892 --> 01:20:46,657
Now, it won't solve everything, but it will help.

1150
01:20:46,885 --> 01:20:49,078
You will continue to grow stronger.

1151
01:20:50,860 --> 01:20:51,583
Thank you.

1152
01:20:54,122 --> 01:20:58,486
As for the others, there are many who are
injured, but they're safe for the time being.

1153
01:20:59,602 --> 01:21:01,113
So don't strain yourself.

1154
01:21:01,257 --> 01:21:02,700
Make sure to rest up.

1155
01:21:07,796 --> 01:21:09,054
Thank you. I will.

1156
01:21:10,251 --> 01:21:10,767
Good.

1157
01:21:38,810 --> 01:21:41,431
<i>Those eyes. He's Upper Three.</i>

1158
01:21:42,063 --> 01:21:43,584
<i>What's he doing here?</i>

1159
01:21:56,797 --> 01:21:58,123
<i>Flame Breathing.</i>

1160
01:21:58,420 --> 01:21:59,488
<i>Second Form...</i>

1161
01:22:01,490 --> 01:22:03,138
<i>Rising Scorching Sun!</i>

1162
01:22:13,161 --> 01:22:14,934
That's a fine sword.

1163
01:22:16,858 --> 01:22:21,166
<i>His speed of regeneration and
sheer malice behind his attack.</i>

1164
01:22:21,459 --> 01:22:23,436
<i>So this is an Upper Rank.</i>

1165
01:22:24,096 --> 01:22:27,111
Why would you go after a wounded person first over me?

1166
01:22:28,828 --> 01:22:32,600
I thought that he'd get in the
way of our little chitchat is all.

1167
01:22:33,340 --> 01:22:35,303
What is it you would like to discuss?

1168
01:22:35,970 --> 01:22:37,849
While this is our first time meeting,

1169
01:22:37,936 --> 01:22:39,669
I already dislike you.

1170
01:22:40,356 --> 01:22:41,538
Is that right?

1171
01:22:41,970 --> 01:22:44,574
Well, I dislike weak human beings.

1172
01:22:44,813 --> 01:22:47,200
The mere sight of them makes my skin crawl.

1173
01:22:48,073 --> 01:22:51,903
If that is the case, I do not
believe we will ever get along.

1174
01:22:53,429 --> 01:22:55,886
Be that as it may, let me make you an offer.

1175
01:22:56,274 --> 01:22:58,956
Why don't you become a demon as well?

1176
01:22:59,216 --> 01:23:00,444
No, thanks.

1177
01:23:00,989 --> 01:23:04,113
I can tell just by looking at you that you're strong.

1178
01:23:04,287 --> 01:23:05,928
A Hashira, huh?

1179
01:23:06,351 --> 01:23:09,760
Your fighting spirit has been tempered like quality steel.

1180
01:23:10,133 --> 01:23:11,173
Your name?

1181
01:23:11,753 --> 01:23:15,161
I'm the Flame Hashira, Kyojuro Rengoku.

1182
01:23:16,267 --> 01:23:17,574
I am Akaza.

1183
01:23:18,262 --> 01:23:24,407
Kyojuro, let me tell you why, despite
being a Hashira, your strength is not enough.

1184
01:23:24,887 --> 01:23:26,802
Because you're merely human,

1185
01:23:27,229 --> 01:23:29,882
destined to grow old and eventually die.

1186
01:23:31,467 --> 01:23:33,714
Become a demon, Kyojuro.

1187
01:23:34,689 --> 01:23:40,597
Doing so would allow you to better
yourself for another hundred, even 200 years.

1188
01:23:42,617 --> 01:23:44,685
<i>Of all the demons I've met so far,</i>

1189
01:23:44,904 --> 01:23:47,266
<i>he smells the most like Kibutsuji!</i>

1190
01:23:47,946 --> 01:23:49,535
<i>I have to help fight him!</i>

1191
01:23:50,708 --> 01:23:53,397
Both growing old and passing way,

1192
01:23:53,782 --> 01:23:56,532
these are things that make being human beautiful.

1193
01:23:57,473 --> 01:23:59,739
Those may seem like weaknesses to you,

1194
01:24:00,425 --> 01:24:03,962
but our lives are all the more
precious and honorable because of them.

1195
01:24:05,572 --> 01:24:07,511
You see, true strength

1196
01:24:07,536 --> 01:24:09,878
does not just refer to the physical body.

1197
01:24:14,397 --> 01:24:16,016
This boy is not weak.

1198
01:24:17,966 --> 01:24:19,300
Don't insult him.

1199
01:24:19,933 --> 01:24:21,192
Let me be clear.

1200
01:24:21,765 --> 01:24:24,487
The two of us will never see eye to eye.

1201
01:24:25,531 --> 01:24:29,265
No matter what twisted reasons you give, I will not yield.

1202
01:24:34,361 --> 01:24:35,234
I see.

1203
01:24:38,246 --> 01:24:40,044
Technique Development.

1204
01:24:41,082 --> 01:24:43,016
Destructive Death, Compass Needle.

1205
01:24:58,720 --> 01:25:01,096
I guess I'll just have to kill you then.

1206
01:25:15,359 --> 01:25:17,566
<i>I can't keep track of either of them!</i>

1207
01:25:18,149 --> 01:25:22,572
In all my years, I've never
gotten to kill a Flame Hashira!

1208
01:25:22,837 --> 01:25:25,773
No one has yet to take me up on my offer, either.

1209
01:25:30,177 --> 01:25:31,919
Why do you think that is?

1210
01:25:31,944 --> 01:25:36,274
As a fellow master of the martial
arts, I just can't comprehend it.

1211
01:25:36,767 --> 01:25:40,075
Not when only the chosen ones can become demons!

1212
01:25:45,201 --> 01:25:49,366
Watching the hideous decline of
someone blessed with your powers,

1213
01:25:49,792 --> 01:25:52,562
it pains me more than you know!

1214
01:25:52,755 --> 01:25:56,888
While you're still young and
strong... your life should be cut short.

1215
01:25:59,328 --> 01:26:00,807
Destructive Death...

1216
01:26:01,989 --> 01:26:02,786
Air Type!

1217
01:26:16,504 --> 01:26:17,686
<i>In that case...</i>

1218
01:26:19,923 --> 01:26:21,347
Flame Breathing technique.

1219
01:26:21,881 --> 01:26:22,836
Fourth Form,

1220
01:26:23,316 --> 01:26:25,100
Blooming Flame Undulation!

1221
01:26:27,347 --> 01:26:30,778
<i>If he strikes the air, the attack will still reach me.</i>

1222
01:26:33,763 --> 01:26:35,819
<i>The strikes travel instantly.</i>

1223
01:26:42,359 --> 01:26:46,341
<i>I can't slice his head off if I continue
fighting him at a distance like this.</i>

1224
01:26:47,116 --> 01:26:48,047
<i>Very well.</i>

1225
01:26:53,667 --> 01:26:55,149
<i>Close combat, it is!</i>

1226
01:26:55,862 --> 01:26:58,517
Those reflexes! Brilliant!

1227
01:27:01,351 --> 01:27:05,031
Those breathtaking sword skills will be lost, too!

1228
01:27:05,056 --> 01:27:07,598
Doesn't that thought make you sad, Kyojuro?

1229
01:27:07,905 --> 01:27:10,704
They are simply aspects of being a human being!

1230
01:27:10,729 --> 01:27:11,757
Why would it?

1231
01:27:12,871 --> 01:27:14,328
Stay there!

1232
01:27:14,721 --> 01:27:16,982
We can't reopen that wound of yours!

1233
01:27:17,007 --> 01:27:18,369
It'll kill you!

1234
01:27:19,494 --> 01:27:21,663
Don't bother with that weakling!

1235
01:27:22,212 --> 01:27:23,883
Show me your strength!

1236
01:27:26,961 --> 01:27:28,842
Keep your eyes on me.

1237
01:27:40,795 --> 01:27:43,047
Such skilled movement.

1238
01:27:48,661 --> 01:27:49,721
Rengoku!

1239
01:27:49,838 --> 01:27:51,416
Watch out, Bug Eyes!

1240
01:27:54,838 --> 01:27:57,506
You sure you won't turn into a demon?

1241
01:28:00,895 --> 01:28:05,559
Think of it this way. If you did, we
could spar with each other endlessly.

1242
01:28:09,536 --> 01:28:12,086
Imagine how much stronger we'd become!

1243
01:28:13,992 --> 01:28:14,865
Never.

1244
01:28:15,604 --> 01:28:17,400
Let me make this clear.

1245
01:28:17,846 --> 01:28:19,503
I do not like you.

1246
01:28:22,528 --> 01:28:24,402
I will not become a demon!

1247
01:28:25,440 --> 01:28:26,746
<i>Flame Breathing.</i>

1248
01:28:28,151 --> 01:28:29,541
Third Form!

1249
01:28:29,566 --> 01:28:31,877
Blazing Universe!

1250
01:28:34,623 --> 01:28:37,024
What a magnificent attack!

1251
01:28:38,337 --> 01:28:40,914
Destructive Death, Air Type!

1252
01:28:49,544 --> 01:28:51,286
<i>I wanna join the fight,</i>

1253
01:28:51,311 --> 01:28:54,916
<i>but they're moving so fast, I can't find an opening!</i>

1254
01:28:55,130 --> 01:28:57,610
<i>These two are on a whole other level!</i>

1255
01:28:58,104 --> 01:29:01,694
<i>Getting between them would get me killed for sure.</i>

1256
01:29:02,301 --> 01:29:04,736
<i>Even if I did find an opportunity,</i>

1257
01:29:04,828 --> 01:29:07,417
<i>I know I'd only end up slowing him down.</i>

1258
01:29:10,799 --> 01:29:12,281
Mr. Rengoku...

1259
01:29:16,990 --> 01:29:18,789
This struggle is futile!

1260
01:29:19,076 --> 01:29:23,086
Continuing this meaningless assault
will only result in one outcome,

1261
01:29:23,172 --> 01:29:24,047
your death!

1262
01:29:33,858 --> 01:29:36,751
<i>Flame Breathing. First Form, Unknowing Fire!</i>

1263
01:29:39,139 --> 01:29:41,314
Killing you now would be a waste.

1264
01:29:41,595 --> 01:29:43,784
You haven't reached your peak yet.

1265
01:29:49,973 --> 01:29:51,219
Second Form...

1266
01:29:52,232 --> 01:29:53,912
Rising Scorching Sun!

1267
01:29:55,441 --> 01:29:57,733
In just a few short years, your abilities

1268
01:29:57,765 --> 01:30:00,688
would be sharpened to an even finer point.

1269
01:30:12,844 --> 01:30:15,446
Third Form, Blazing Universe!

1270
01:30:17,148 --> 01:30:20,299
Fourth Form, Blooming Flame Undulation!

1271
01:30:22,331 --> 01:30:24,203
Destructive Death...

1272
01:30:25,576 --> 01:30:28,993
Fifth Form, Flame Tiger!

1273
01:30:31,640 --> 01:30:32,621
Disorder!

1274
01:30:37,664 --> 01:30:39,724
Come at me!

1275
01:30:55,102 --> 01:30:55,755
Wait.

1276
01:30:56,205 --> 01:30:58,801
Is that it? Did he win?!

1277
01:31:27,450 --> 01:31:28,292
<i>No way.</i>

1278
01:31:35,278 --> 01:31:36,279
<i>It can't be.</i>

1279
01:31:44,231 --> 01:31:45,994
Don't tell me it's over.

1280
01:31:47,486 --> 01:31:49,374
I won't have you die on me.

1281
01:32:06,007 --> 01:32:07,293
<i>Mr. Rengoku.</i>

1282
01:32:08,123 --> 01:32:09,166
<i>Rengoku!</i>

1283
01:32:12,087 --> 01:32:13,116
<i>Rengoku!</i>

1284
01:32:18,384 --> 01:32:24,159
Don't you see that fighting to death in that
frail human body will never measure up to mine?

1285
01:32:25,849 --> 01:32:29,206
Those impressive attacks that you inflicted upon me

1286
01:32:29,231 --> 01:32:31,651
have already healed completely.

1287
01:32:32,464 --> 01:32:34,152
You, on the other hand...

1288
01:32:34,571 --> 01:32:41,412
a smashed left eye, shattered ribs, damage
to the internal organs... all irreparable.

1289
01:32:41,959 --> 01:32:44,662
If you were a demon, you'd heal in the blink of an eye,

1290
01:32:45,309 --> 01:32:48,006
and those wounds would be but mere scratches.

1291
01:32:48,869 --> 01:32:52,529
In the end, a human can never surpass a demon.

1292
01:32:55,297 --> 01:32:56,841
<i>I want to go help him.</i>

1293
01:33:00,111 --> 01:33:02,275
<i>But I don't have the strength to move.</i>

1294
01:33:02,888 --> 01:33:07,627
<i>This injury and using Hinokami
Kagura have taken their toll.</i>

1295
01:33:21,216 --> 01:33:23,378
So this is how it is, then.

1296
01:33:25,500 --> 01:33:26,131
I...

1297
01:33:27,625 --> 01:33:30,325
I will see my duty fulfilled!

1298
01:33:30,845 --> 01:33:34,215
No matter what it takes, no one shall die here!

1299
01:33:35,645 --> 01:33:38,591
<i>I'll inflict as much damage as quickly as possible.</i>

1300
01:33:39,458 --> 01:33:40,655
<i>Flame Breathing.</i>

1301
01:33:40,943 --> 01:33:42,248
<i>Esoteric Art!</i>

1302
01:33:48,436 --> 01:33:50,629
What an impressive fighting spirit.

1303
01:33:50,776 --> 01:33:53,499
To press on, despite your bodily injuries!

1304
01:33:53,686 --> 01:33:55,559
That brilliant strength of mind!

1305
01:33:55,899 --> 01:33:57,899
And that ironclad stance!

1306
01:34:01,079 --> 01:34:03,204
Now you have to become a demon!

1307
01:34:03,409 --> 01:34:04,838
Just imagine it!

1308
01:34:04,998 --> 01:34:08,219
We'd be able to fight each other for the rest of eternity!

1309
01:34:08,245 --> 01:34:09,808
<i>Set your heart ablaze.</i>

1310
01:34:10,206 --> 01:34:12,208
<i>Overcome your limits.</i>

1311
01:34:13,705 --> 01:34:15,638
I am the Flame Hashira,

1312
01:34:15,970 --> 01:34:17,742
Kyojuro Rengoku!

1313
01:34:18,382 --> 01:34:21,860
Ninth Form, Rengoku!

1314
01:34:22,460 --> 01:34:25,265
Destructive Death, Annihilation Type!

1315
01:34:42,246 --> 01:34:43,720
Rengoku!

1316
01:35:16,732 --> 01:35:17,875
<i>Mr. Rengoku.</i>

1317
01:35:23,359 --> 01:35:24,298
<i>Where is he?</i>

1318
01:35:27,325 --> 01:35:27,845
<i>There.</i>

1319
01:35:28,725 --> 01:35:30,731
Did he win?

1320
01:35:41,954 --> 01:35:45,280
Kyojuro, you must know this wound will kill you!

1321
01:35:45,613 --> 01:35:46,624
Save yourself.

1322
01:35:46,703 --> 01:35:48,569
Say that you'll become a demon!

1323
01:35:49,089 --> 01:35:50,340
Can't you see?!

1324
01:35:50,725 --> 01:35:53,368
Your strength makes you truly special!

1325
01:36:06,658 --> 01:36:07,484
Kyojuro.

1326
01:36:07,857 --> 01:36:09,159
Yes, what is it, Mother?

1327
01:36:10,506 --> 01:36:12,078
I want to ask you something,

1328
01:36:12,825 --> 01:36:14,733
and I want you to answer honestly.

1329
01:36:15,793 --> 01:36:17,207
Do you know why it is

1330
01:36:17,541 --> 01:36:20,470
you were born with greater strength than so many others?

1331
01:36:22,977 --> 01:36:23,424
Uh...

1332
01:36:25,172 --> 01:36:26,319
no, ma'am, I don't.

1333
01:36:27,139 --> 01:36:29,372
It is so that you can protect the weak.

1334
01:36:31,345 --> 01:36:35,149
Those who are born blessed with
more bountiful gifts than others

1335
01:36:35,683 --> 01:36:39,007
are obligated to use those
gifts for the sake of the world,

1336
01:36:39,273 --> 01:36:41,958
for all of our fellow brothers and sisters.

1337
01:36:43,325 --> 01:36:50,481
You must never use that God-given strength to
bring harm to mankind or for your own selfish desires.

1338
01:36:52,078 --> 01:36:54,411
It is the duty of those born strong

1339
01:36:54,782 --> 01:36:57,163
to help those who may be less fortunate,

1340
01:36:57,943 --> 01:37:01,982
a responsibility you must carry onward with due purpose.

1341
01:37:02,976 --> 01:37:06,102
Be sure you never forget that.

1342
01:37:06,928 --> 01:37:07,662
I won't!

1343
01:37:15,043 --> 01:37:15,524
Uh...

1344
01:37:25,059 --> 01:37:25,939
Kyojuro...

1345
01:37:26,859 --> 01:37:28,617
I don't have much time left.

1346
01:37:29,970 --> 01:37:32,368
Having such a strong, gentle child...

1347
01:37:32,775 --> 01:37:34,062
was a true blessing.

1348
01:37:36,610 --> 01:37:37,884
I believe in you.

1349
01:37:51,737 --> 01:37:52,444
<i>Mother...</i>

1350
01:37:52,830 --> 01:37:56,986
<i>it was I who was blessed to have
been born to such a woman as you.</i>

1351
01:38:06,438 --> 01:38:07,631
<i>He stopped it?</i>

1352
01:38:07,924 --> 01:38:09,683
<i>What unbelievable strength!</i>

1353
01:38:10,217 --> 01:38:12,949
<i>And even after I've skewered his body with my arm!</i>

1354
01:38:15,109 --> 01:38:17,582
<i>Damn it. The sun will rise soon.</i>

1355
01:38:19,048 --> 01:38:21,177
<i>I have to kill him and make my escape!</i>

1356
01:38:22,955 --> 01:38:25,039
<i>Why can't I pull my arm out?</i>

1357
01:38:27,581 --> 01:38:29,185
<i>I won't let you escape.</i>

1358
01:38:36,579 --> 01:38:39,888
<i>I know Mr. Rengoku ordered me to stay back,</i>

1359
01:38:41,661 --> 01:38:43,847
<i>but I just can't any longer!</i>

1360
01:38:45,160 --> 01:38:46,817
<i>This is my only chance.</i>

1361
01:38:46,896 --> 01:38:49,730
<i>I have to slice that demon's head off, and fast!</i>

1362
01:38:52,478 --> 01:38:53,971
<i>The sun is rising.</i>

1363
01:38:54,571 --> 01:38:56,459
<i>I have to get away!</i>

1364
01:38:57,483 --> 01:38:58,663
<i>Let go of me.</i>

1365
01:38:58,698 --> 01:39:00,529
<i>Let go of me!</i>

1366
01:39:09,944 --> 01:39:11,759
<i>I won't let go!</i>

1367
01:39:12,033 --> 01:39:15,029
<i>Not 'til I remove your head from your shoulders!</i>

1368
01:39:17,920 --> 01:39:20,481
Let go!

1369
01:39:24,681 --> 01:39:26,257
Inosuke, move!

1370
01:39:26,464 --> 01:39:27,145
Huh?

1371
01:39:27,170 --> 01:39:30,102
If we don't help him now, it'll be too late!

1372
01:39:33,881 --> 01:39:35,121
Beast Breathing!

1373
01:39:35,414 --> 01:39:36,651
Fang One...

1374
01:39:37,012 --> 01:39:38,531
Pierce!

1375
01:39:56,147 --> 01:39:59,134
<i>I've got to find sanctuary from the sunlight.</i>

1376
01:40:10,268 --> 01:40:11,710
<i>That took too long.</i>

1377
01:40:11,933 --> 01:40:13,694
<i>I've got to get away from the sun!</i>

1378
01:40:20,922 --> 01:40:22,735
Don't run away!

1379
01:40:23,335 --> 01:40:25,328
I'm not done with you, coward!

1380
01:40:25,367 --> 01:40:27,017
Turn and face me!

1381
01:40:29,677 --> 01:40:32,404
<i>What the hell are you babbling about, kid?</i>

1382
01:40:33,030 --> 01:40:35,734
<i>Don't you have a brain inside that head of yours?</i>

1383
01:40:36,168 --> 01:40:38,162
<i>I'm not running away from you.</i>

1384
01:40:38,382 --> 01:40:40,362
<i>I'm running from the sun!</i>

1385
01:40:40,661 --> 01:40:43,920
<i>And besides, this battle's already been decided!</i>

1386
01:40:44,207 --> 01:40:47,408
<i>With a wound like that, he'll die before long.</i>

1387
01:40:50,153 --> 01:40:54,802
Don't forget that the Demon Slayer Corps is
always fighting you demons in the dead of night,

1388
01:40:54,855 --> 01:40:56,630
where you have the advantage!

1389
01:40:56,655 --> 01:40:58,397
We're not like you at all!

1390
01:40:58,842 --> 01:41:00,609
We don't regenerate as fast,

1391
01:41:01,108 --> 01:41:03,904
and when we lose a limb, it's gone for good!

1392
01:41:04,550 --> 01:41:07,109
Don't run away, you bastard!

1393
01:41:07,183 --> 01:41:09,804
You're a coward, a coward!

1394
01:41:10,624 --> 01:41:14,098
Mr. Rengoku is stronger than you'll ever hope to be!

1395
01:41:15,055 --> 01:41:16,275
Much stronger!

1396
01:41:16,715 --> 01:41:18,442
You didn't win against him!

1397
01:41:18,879 --> 01:41:20,967
He kept everyone safe!

1398
01:41:21,106 --> 01:41:24,411
He fought to the very end so no one would die!

1399
01:41:24,498 --> 01:41:26,161
You're the one who lost!

1400
01:41:26,541 --> 01:41:30,248
Rengoku is the true victor!

1401
01:42:05,207 --> 01:42:06,789
Don't work yourself up like that.

1402
01:42:13,287 --> 01:42:14,787
You would reopen your wound...

1403
01:42:15,938 --> 01:42:17,500
and that would be very bad.

1404
01:42:19,012 --> 01:42:21,009
You dying, my young Kamado,

1405
01:42:21,838 --> 01:42:23,417
would truly spell my defeat.

1406
01:42:25,879 --> 01:42:27,039
Mr. Rengoku.

1407
01:42:28,580 --> 01:42:29,567
Come here, lad.

1408
01:42:30,459 --> 01:42:32,392
Let us speak one last time.

1409
01:42:50,814 --> 01:42:52,740
When I was dreaming of the past...

1410
01:42:54,448 --> 01:42:56,155
there was something I remembered.

1411
01:42:57,794 --> 01:42:59,185
My old residence...

1412
01:43:00,136 --> 01:43:01,838
you should go pay it a visit.

1413
01:43:03,849 --> 01:43:06,924
There are notes left by the previous Flame Hashira there.

1414
01:43:09,048 --> 01:43:11,852
I recall my father used to read them often,

1415
01:43:12,338 --> 01:43:15,237
but I'm afraid I don't know their contents myself.

1416
01:43:17,534 --> 01:43:19,156
Within those notes...

1417
01:43:19,916 --> 01:43:22,113
you may find the dance you mentioned,

1418
01:43:23,472 --> 01:43:25,239
the Hinokami Kagura.

1419
01:43:27,101 --> 01:43:29,138
Please! Mr. Rengoku...

1420
01:43:29,418 --> 01:43:30,440
enough of that.

1421
01:43:30,817 --> 01:43:32,577
Just think about yourself now.

1422
01:43:33,231 --> 01:43:35,507
Can you heal up with a breathing technique?

1423
01:43:36,021 --> 01:43:36,729
No.

1424
01:43:37,272 --> 01:43:39,399
Very soon, I'll be dead.

1425
01:43:42,045 --> 01:43:43,462
Before that happens,

1426
01:43:43,904 --> 01:43:45,742
I need you to hear me out.

1427
01:43:47,198 --> 01:43:49,519
I have a younger brother named Senjuro.

1428
01:43:50,704 --> 01:43:52,778
Please tell him to follow his heart

1429
01:43:53,709 --> 01:43:56,101
and walk down the path he feels is right.

1430
01:43:59,640 --> 01:44:01,000
And tell my father...

1431
01:44:02,191 --> 01:44:04,237
that I want him to look after himself.

1432
01:44:07,269 --> 01:44:08,295
And lastly...

1433
01:44:08,991 --> 01:44:10,289
about your sister...

1434
01:44:12,605 --> 01:44:14,684
know that I believe in her.

1435
01:44:16,139 --> 01:44:18,523
I accept her as part of our ranks.

1436
01:44:21,115 --> 01:44:25,864
Your sister shed blood to protect the
people inside that train from demons.

1437
01:44:27,273 --> 01:44:28,944
And anyone who does that,

1438
01:44:29,231 --> 01:44:34,430
regardless of what is said to the contrary,
is a rightful member of the Demon Slayer Corps.

1439
01:44:36,245 --> 01:44:37,936
So hold your head high.

1440
01:44:43,423 --> 01:44:45,353
If you are feeling disheartened,

1441
01:44:45,975 --> 01:44:47,944
that you are somehow not enough...

1442
01:44:50,319 --> 01:44:51,785
set your heart ablaze.

1443
01:44:55,044 --> 01:44:57,117
Dry your eyes, and look ahead.

1444
01:44:58,769 --> 01:45:01,004
You may feel like digging your heels in,

1445
01:45:01,891 --> 01:45:04,288
but the flow of time waits for no one.

1446
01:45:05,287 --> 01:45:08,300
It won't patiently stand by as you grieve.

1447
01:45:10,506 --> 01:45:12,654
Don't feel bad that I'm going to die.

1448
01:45:13,727 --> 01:45:17,602
As a Hashira, it's natural I'd protect you all.

1449
01:45:19,181 --> 01:45:21,880
The young buds must be allowed to bloom.

1450
01:45:23,159 --> 01:45:25,730
Any other Hashira would have done the same as I.

1451
01:45:27,249 --> 01:45:28,301
Young Kamado...

1452
01:45:30,198 --> 01:45:31,099
Young Boar...

1453
01:45:32,714 --> 01:45:33,874
Boy of Yellow...

1454
01:45:35,692 --> 01:45:37,538
you must continue to grow.

1455
01:45:38,603 --> 01:45:43,562
And eventually you will lend your
aid by becoming the next Hashira.

1456
01:45:45,429 --> 01:45:46,597
I believe...

1457
01:45:47,750 --> 01:45:50,612
in each and every one of you.

1458
01:46:17,012 --> 01:46:17,823
<i>Mother.</i>

1459
01:46:22,171 --> 01:46:23,195
<i>Did I do well?</i>

1460
01:46:25,912 --> 01:46:30,211
<i>The responsibility I-I took upon myself to fulfill...</i>

1461
01:46:31,020 --> 01:46:32,187
<i>was I successful?</i>

1462
01:46:41,943 --> 01:46:44,228
<i>I'm so proud of you, my son.</i>

1463
01:47:20,749 --> 01:47:22,636
When the train went off the rails,

1464
01:47:23,049 --> 01:47:25,648
Mr. Rengoku used a bunch of his techniques.

1465
01:47:26,962 --> 01:47:30,897
That must be how we somehow
avoided suffering any casualties.

1466
01:47:33,142 --> 01:47:34,166
It must be.

1467
01:47:36,412 --> 01:47:38,105
I can't believe he's gone.

1468
01:47:38,942 --> 01:47:41,170
Was it really an Upper Rank demon?

1469
01:47:41,970 --> 01:47:42,541
Yeah.

1470
01:47:43,829 --> 01:47:46,053
Why would something like that come here,

1471
01:47:46,755 --> 01:47:49,348
something that strong? I don't get it.

1472
01:47:53,756 --> 01:47:55,130
I'm so frustrated.

1473
01:47:57,393 --> 01:47:59,689
Soon as I manage to break through one wall...

1474
01:48:01,143 --> 01:48:05,113
it feels like I just hit an even higher, thicker wall.

1475
01:48:07,422 --> 01:48:11,781
And all the while, I can hear the sounds
of my heroes fighting just beyond it...

1476
01:48:13,008 --> 01:48:15,311
but I can't make it over to join them!

1477
01:48:16,904 --> 01:48:19,648
If I'm still here fumbling around in the dark...

1478
01:48:21,362 --> 01:48:22,589
how can I ever...

1479
01:48:25,558 --> 01:48:29,504
Is becoming someone like him even possible for me?

1480
01:48:40,168 --> 01:48:42,567
Stop blubbering like a little baby!

1481
01:48:44,140 --> 01:48:48,391
This "can I or can't I" talk is really pissing me off!

1482
01:48:48,864 --> 01:48:51,062
He already said he believes in you,

1483
01:48:51,222 --> 01:48:53,979
so you just have to worry about how to get there!

1484
01:48:54,293 --> 01:48:57,685
All living things just go back to the earth when they die!

1485
01:48:58,112 --> 01:49:00,991
Feeling sorry for yourself isn't gonna change that!

1486
01:49:01,244 --> 01:49:03,604
Remember what Bug Eyes said to you!

1487
01:49:04,024 --> 01:49:09,744
No matter how pathetic or humiliated
you feel, you just gotta keep on living!

1488
01:49:10,144 --> 01:49:11,794
But you're crying, too.

1489
01:49:12,400 --> 01:49:15,586
I can see all the tears coming
out of that headpiece of yours.

1490
01:49:16,170 --> 01:49:18,157
I am not crying!

1491
01:49:28,965 --> 01:49:32,173
Come on! Let's go train our asses off!

1492
01:50:15,709 --> 01:50:16,964
Is that right?

1493
01:50:17,232 --> 01:50:19,105
Mr. Rengoku has...

1494
01:50:39,767 --> 01:50:41,567
An Upper Rank demon...

1495
01:50:41,904 --> 01:50:43,938
even Rengoku couldn't kill it.

1496
01:50:49,418 --> 01:50:51,196
I won't believe it.

1497
01:50:58,227 --> 01:51:00,007
<i>Namu Amida Butsu.</i>

1498
01:51:06,920 --> 01:51:08,844
Those repulsive demons...

1499
01:51:09,091 --> 01:51:11,003
I'll exterminate them all.

1500
01:51:19,155 --> 01:51:20,712
Is that so?

1501
01:51:30,180 --> 01:51:34,728
Not even a single one of those
200 passengers lost their lives?

1502
01:51:35,660 --> 01:51:38,063
He did a splendid job indeed.

1503
01:51:38,246 --> 01:51:39,650
A remarkable child.

1504
01:51:41,503 --> 01:51:43,239
I feel no sadness.

1505
01:51:43,885 --> 01:51:46,573
My life will soon reach its end as well.

1506
01:51:49,745 --> 01:51:54,310
And then I'll be able to see Kyojuro and the others again

1507
01:51:54,664 --> 01:51:55,999
in the world after.

1508
01:52:07,963 --> 01:52:09,291
Mr. Rengoku.

1509
01:52:11,000 --> 01:52:12,299
Rengoku.

1510
01:52:15,316 --> 01:52:16,782
Rengoku!

